name: Vikings
summary: The Minnesota Vikings defeated the Indianapolis Colts 21-14 in Week 9 of the NFL season, ending a two-game losing streak. The game was played on "Sunday Night Football" and was available to watch on various platforms. Quarterback Sam Darnold had three turnovers for the Vikings, but they still managed to outlast the Colts. The Vikings' defense played aggressively against the Colts, who started Joe Flacco at quarterback. Minnesota's playoff chances are still alive, and they will need to continue to perform well in the coming weeks.

name: Harvey Epstein
summary: A recent "Saturday Night Live" sketch has brought unprecedented attention to a New York City politician named Harvey Epstein. In response, the real Harvey Epstein has expressed amusement and taken the opportunity to promote his campaign for New York City Council. The politician has stated that while he realizes the sketch was intended as a joke, he appreciates the free publicity it has brought to his campaign. Various news outlets have covered Epstein's reaction to the sketch, highlighting both the humor and the boost it has given to his candidacy.
